### FreeEdu API Http Requests Documentation
# You can use VS Code REST Client or IntelliJ HTTP Client to execute these requests.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

### Register User (STUDENT)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "student01@example.com",
  "username": "student01",
  "password": "strongPassword123",
  "role": "STUDENT"
}

###

### Register User (ADMIN)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin01@example.com",
  "username": "admin01",
  "password": "strongPassword123",
  "role": "ADMIN"
}

###

### Login User
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "student01@example.com",
  "password": "strongPassword123"
}

###

# Token is automatically extracted from the login response above
@authToken = {{login.response.body.token}}

### Example Protected Endpoint
# Use this structure once you add protected API endpoints in the future
# GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/me
# Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
